 Greetings to you all,<br>
<br>
I have been an avid roleplayer for most of my life, and was greatly dissapointed in the fact that roleplay is mostly non-existant in EQ.<br>
<br>
Recently I was told about your guild and I heard about some great stuff that the RP community of Brell has been doing, so I decided to dig a little deeper  <br>
<br>
But my problem is this, my main character Jairn, is a member of ET and most of my time is eaten up taking part in raids etc. However, I would love to put my wizard Tzinn, a level 18th Wizard up for membership for your guild. I would only to be able to log Tzinn on from time to time, and therefore couldnt really be an active member with regards to raids etc.<br>
<br>
There also a couple things I would like to know  <br>
<br>
1. What are your requirements for membership, is the guild restricted to evil races only, or can I play that gnome slave?  <br>
<br>
2. How is roleplay handled, is it strictly in groups or meeting to face to face? In guildchat is it constant roleplay?<br>
<br>
3. What time is everyone mostly on? Being a brit, this could be a problem  <br>
<br>
I recently took a break from Brell recently and went to Vallon Zek pvp teams server. There I made a troll shaman and was hunting the newbie areas. After a while, a noticed that a troll was being jumped by some frogs, so after scratching my butt, I ran over and threw him a couple of heals. This turned into a 15 minute roleplay session between us and it was one of the best times I've ever had playing EQ  <br>
<br>
Looking forward to hearing from you,<br>
<br>
Jairn Silmarian.<br>
Bearer of Swiftwind and Earthcaller.<br>
Protector of Faydark.<br>
<br>
