 hi Jairn! The requirements are mostly quest based. You must find a sponsor, then you must complete a fairly easy quest. Non-Teir'dal are allowed to join but only in a diminished capacity. They will not be allowed to hold officer positions generally. As we are fond of saying though--our lowest tiller (non Teir'dal) will be greater than a king in the days when Norrath is returned to shadow. The restriction on Non-Teir'dal entry is unanimous Triad consent. I dont see that as much of a problem in most cases.<br>
<br>
Roleplay varies a lot in the harvest. Some days we are really on and roleplay guild, group, shout and say. Other days we are fairly easy with a lot of ooc talk going on in guild. I think the important part is that we all have developed character backgrounds and try to maintain a certain personna. We also have several guilds that we interact with regularly and generally I would say we are weaving two to three roleplay plots along at a time with various members of the guild. At our meetings recently we have nearly always had some great roleplay.<br>
<br>
As for time, we all play at really different times of day. There are a cpl other brits with us, and their are ppl who only play in what would be your morning. We try to come together for raids and meetings but it isnt always possible for us to get everyone there.<br>
<br>
